The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, June 20, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Chinsurah, June 19: Ten-year-old Prasenjit Singha and his brother Sanjib, 8, were crushed under the wheels of a bus that mounted the pavement at Chandernagore this morning.

 Police said the driver of the Serampore-bound bus lost control trying to overtake another. A mob tried to set the bus ablaze but the police intervened. Residents blocked GT Road in protest against rash driving. 

 Calcutta: A man allegedly seen roaming the Park Street area since Sunday evening was arrested at night. Police caught Mohammed Iqtat, 30, with a revolver and several cartridges.

 Calcutta: A truck hit an autorickshaw on Jessore Road near Birati around 9.30 pm on Sunday. The auto went on to hit a rickshawpuller standing on the roadside. He was killed immediately. Another man died at RG Kar Hospital later.

 Howrah: Eighteen-year-old Priyanka Singha Roy was allegedly abducted at gunpoint from her home in Uluberia on Saturday night in the presence of her mother and sister. The mother, Purnima, said three youths carrying revolvers and daggers entered the house around 8 pm and took her away. 

 Behrampore: Police on Saturday night rescued four children, who were allegedly being smuggled to north India, from the bus terminus here. Residents were attracted by the sobs of three girls and a boy aged 8-11. The children from Jalangi, 250 km from Calcutta, had been promised a fun trip to Delhi. 




